The Australian New South Wales, State Of Government announced 11th that it would spend a $200 million ($ 154 million) on the largest renovation since the famous Sydney Opera House was built, Xinhua news agency said.
The New South Wales, State Of Government said the repairs would not alter the shell shape of the opera house.
The Sydney Opera House is one of Sydney's landmark buildings, designed by Danish architect 约恩·乌特松, completed in 1973 and receives about 8 million visitors each year.
Sydney Symphony Orchestra general manager 罗里·杰夫斯 believes that the Sydney Opera House will use this transformation to play a "turnaround", become "the world's best acoustics one of the concert hall."
